entries.meaning: (video games, slang) The final boss character in a game.
examples: The original Ultima was a kill-the-foozle type of game where the goal was to destroy the Gem of Power, which was held by an evil wizard named Mondain.

verbs.description: foozle (third-person singular simple present foozles, present participle foozling, simple past and past participle foozled)

entries.meaning: To do something clumsily or awkwardly; to bungle.
examples: Every baseball fan is acquainted with the sarcastic reminder, "two hands are the fashion nowadays," often hurled at the infielder who foozles an attempt at a grandstand play in the form of a one-handed catch.
